At a higher level, (Mann and Yarowsky, 2003) disambiguated personal names by clustering people’s home pages using a TFIDF similarity, and several other researchers have applied clustering at the same level in the context of the entity identification problem (Bilenko et al., 2003; McCallum and Wellner, 2003; Li et al., 2004).
